            <section>
               <title value="Hospital Course"/>
               <code>
                  <coding>
                     <system value="http://loinc.org"/>
                     <code value="8648-8"/>
                     <display value="Hospital Course"/>
                  </coding>
               </code>
               <text>
                  <status value="generated"/>
                  <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding the discharge of your 61-year-old male patient, admitted on 25th June 1998 due to substance dependence. Upon admission, a comprehensive psychiatric and somatic assessment was performed, confirming polysubstance dependence syndrome (ICD-10: F19.2). Laboratory investigations revealed markers consistent with chronic substance misuse. During his inpatient stay, the patient underwent medically supervised detoxification, including pharmacological support to manage withdrawal symptoms. Motivational counselling and psychoeducational sessions were initiated, and the patient engaged satisfactorily with the therapeutic programme. By discharge on 8th July 1998, the patient was clinically stabilised with no acute withdrawal symptoms. Outpatient follow-up with addiction services has been arranged. I kindly ask you to support continued engagement with community-based rehabilitation. Please do not hesitate to contact me should further information be required.</div>
               </text>
            </section>
